here is our research: Name: Escape-O-Mania

Purpose: Escape-O-Mania is an escape room that builds on the options that you choose throughout. The better choices you make, the harder the intensity of the course. There will also be an arcade for the younger audience.  

The need: The escape room industry is showing exponential growth, which is due to the consumer demand for interactive entertainment experiences. The global escape room market was valued at approximately $7.8 billion in 2023 and is expected to reach $21.5 billion by 2030 (https://www.strategicmarketresearch.com/market-report/escape-room-market). Some of the key factors are Experiential Entertainment, meaning consumers who are mostly Millennials and Gen Z, who are increasingly looking for something unique, interactive experiences that provide entertainment (https://www.techsciresearch.com/news/17607-escape-room-market), and Technological Integration, which means the incorporation of advanced technologies such as virtual reality (VR) and augmented reality (AR) which enhancing the immersive quality of an experience, attracting a broader audience (https://www.peekpro.com/blog/latest-escape-room-industry-trends-in-2024). Escape-O-Mania's unique approach, where the difficulty adapts based on players' choice, which fulfills new players and seasoned/advanced players, meaning this will enhance replayability and engagement. Additionally, the addition of an arcade appeals to younger audiences, broadening the customer base. 

Target Market and Segmentation: 
Primary Segments
Young Adults (Ages 18 - 34): The demographic represents the top segment of the consumers who would be willing to go to an escape room. Specifically, individuals aged 25-34 make up 40% of the participants, and consumers aged between 18-24 make up about 30%, which totals up to 70% of the escape room audience (https://gitnux.org/escape-room-statistics).
Families with Children: Since there will be an arcade, it will make Escape-O-Mania appealing to families seeking inclusive entertainment options.
Corporate Clients: Companies looking for business meetings and innovative team-building activities can benefit from the adaptive challenges offered.
Teens: Consumers in the age group between 12-17 try to find a way to go out with their friends, and do something entertaining either during break or during an introduction of something new. 

Segmentation Criteria:
Demographic: Factors like age, family status, and occupation
Psychographic: Lifestyle preferences, such as a desire for interactive and challenging experiences
Behavioral: Frequency of seeking group activities, openness to new entertainment forms
Geographic: Residents within a 30-mile radius of Monmouth Junction, NJ, including nearby urban centers

Factors Impacting the Marketing Environment:

Technological Advancements:

The integration of VR and AR is becoming increasingly prevalent in escape rooms, enhancing the immersive experience and attracting tech-savvy customers and online influencers. 

Competitive Landscapes:
	
The escape room market faces saturation in urban areas, making it essential for new businesses to differentiate themselves through unique themes and experiences, meaning our advantage would be the part where the escape room's difficulty changes with more accurate answers.

Economic Factors:
	
		Consumer spending on activities that are fun and challenging can be based on economic conditions 
which can affect attendance rates, so prices can influence a person's standing in the economic structure.

Regulatory Considerations:

Emergency protocols, participant supervision, approval from OSHA, which must be followed due to the Occupational Safety and Health Act of 197, and is responsible for setting and enforcing workplace safety and health standards. We would also need a Business License for operating the business, and finally, we would also need to use Zoning and Land Use regulations since we are establishing a physical location. 

Seasonal Demand:

Escape rooms will change in demand based on seasonal factors, meaning targeting market strategies during off-peak periods. Students who are in high school will have to deal with AP exams, finals, and more like the SAT, especially during college application submissions. For adults, there may be times when the stock market is down or the economy is struggling, resulting in lower pay, which can lead to a lower audience rate. Sometimes, there is a possibility of overlap, meaning an even higher emphasis on the market strategy would be necessary. 

Advantages and disadvantages of individuals vs. family branding + branding strategy (Leo)

Individual branding:
	Advantages 
Unique advertisement for each product 
If one product fails it will not harm the entire brand 
Allows each product to have a different image 
		Disadvantages
High cost 
	
	Family branding: 
		Advantages 
Low cost 
Strong brand identity - displays a clear and consistent image across all products 
Increased recognition - consumers are likely recognize the brand image easily 
		Disadvantages
Low flexibility - it is difficult to advertise individual products 
If one product fails, the entire brand image can be affected 

Branding strategy
	Escape-O-Mania will use a family branding strategy. This strategy will allow the company to build a recognizable brand image while reducing marketing costs, increasing customer loyalty, trust, and credibility. 

Factors of pricing decisions + pricing strategy (Bryce)

Price Skimming - Setting prices high as we open our company, then gradually lowering it to meet more reasonable prices. This will cause people to come back as they will believe they are saving money.

Competitive Pricing - Setting prices equal to our competitors. This is a simple pricing strategy that will allow us to operate freely. 

Psychological Pricing - Setting prices to odd numbers, such as 29.99, this number seems lower, even though it‚Äôs really 30 dollars, it simply looks more attractive. We can also use this method by allowing people to get a ‚Äúfree‚Äù escape room if they purchase two. While we really make a profit from this, as it will lead more people to buy more. 

