Here's a deliberately silly example of psychological pricing that sounds stupid but still works because of how human brains interpret numbers:

Escape Room Price: $30
Special Limited Offer: Only $29.97!

That‚Äôs just 3 cents off, but people actually perceive it as noticeably cheaper‚Äîeven though it's basically the same. It sounds almost like, ‚ÄúWow, it‚Äôs under $30!‚Äù even though in practice, nobody is saving anything meaningful.

Even goofier:

"Limited Deal: $29.99 + Free Mystery Penny Back!"

It sounds absurd, but now you‚Äôve created intrigue and made $29.99 feel even more ‚Äúcleverly priced.‚Äù

Want a few creative price gimmicks for your campaign or something meme-worthy?

